			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello, <BR>
<BR>
I still have the note from 2 years ago when I first started this quest. I was fishing through my bank, cleaning it out and remembered the scroll. I opened it, and noticed that it has changed. Aha! Indeed, the quest had been broken and was now fixed. A new sentence was added that indicated that the scroll had magical lock on it preventing it from being read.<BR>
<BR>
(I deleted a paragraph here, since people have decided to use my information and kept it to themselves. I'm sure someone has already solved this quest). <BR>
<BR>
After finding the NPC and giving him the scroll, it turns out that the quest doesn't end in neriak but somewhere else. Neriak is actually your clue to start from, but the Blue Flame is actually not a place or location, but a victim's revenge against his slayer (great story line here btw). I went to the new location mentioned above, but I'm having a bit of trouble since mobs there train really bad. <BR>
<BR>
I think im on the right track now...<BR>
<BR>
Menalaus on Vallon Zek
